data.text:
1930's western film features an all black cast - a great grade-b western. When Bob Blake and his four singing cowboys go to the Jackson Ranch, they learn that Mr. Jackson is missing. Soon they discover that he's been kidnapped and there might be gold involved. (USA, 1939, B&W, 58 mins, dir. Richard C. Kahn, with Herb Jeffries & Artie Young) (#4097)
